$TSLA it only takes a few hundred thousand shares in PM and a few well-timed buys to surge FOMO into buying 860....then spend the rest of the day killing it. The surge not only ensures they sell some calls to hedge the puts they pay but also cuts into some premium and gets as many puts to close as possible before they start taking it back down. If this goes back to 690, I will have witnessed the MMs use the same one day moonshot scheme it used the first time this hit 790 and flew to 930. It allows them to kill put premiums, shake retail shorts, and kill bear traders while loading the calls and then just algo crush it back down even lower. 

Given the macro situation, if this revisits 690 and doesn't double bottom, then I would look to go long, around 450-550. The only other spot may be worth a bull scalp is if it breaks through and closes above 925. This is a nasty game they are playing while reducing their exposure. Know what you are doing or wait till things make sense.
